"Official Live 101 Proof"  
  Where You Come From  
  
  *Well, here it is...the full tab to Where You Come From. I think this*  
  *is the best Pantera Song to date. Dime tunes his guitar way down*  
  *1 1/2 steps to ***C#***.*  
  *I think he likes that low grinding sound. I know I do!*  
  *Dime uses tap harmonics in the opening verse. These are pretty easy*  
  *to pull off and they sound cool. All you do is keep the last note*  
  *fretted and then tap a harmonic on the fret indicated (usually 12*  
  *frets higher).*  
  *Next comes the best riff. This riff is the baddest. It is pretty*  
  *fast and it has those cool artificial harmonics in it.*  
  *As for the solo I left that for another day.*  
  *The low grinding ***C#*** in the last riff is pure power. I love the way*  
  *this song ends with that ***C#*** and the power chords.*  
  *Have fun and remember to crank the distortion when you play this*  
  *tune!!*  
  *P.S. This is my first tab; I hope you like it!!*  
  
  *tune down to*  
